"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521158","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>The Department does not hold the information requested.</p><p>According to figures from the national census and published by the Office for National Statistics, there were around 166,000 young carers in England in 2011.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-06T14:03:32.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521158/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521158/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521158/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Children: Carers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 24 May 2016 to Question 37692, if she will estimate the number of young carers in each of the last 10 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","38349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521159","Department for Education","false","2016-06-02","<p>It is unacceptable for any child to be victimised, harmed or bullied. All schools are required by law to have a behaviour policy which includes measures to prevent and tackle all forms of bullying. They should exercise their own judgment and develop a consistent approach to monitoring bullying incidents in their school. There is no requirement on schools to record and report incidents of bullying, so the Department does not hold national information on the number of incidents of bullying that take place in schools or online.</p><p> </p><p>The Department provided £1.3 million of funding over twelve months from spring 2015 to three anti-bullying organisations which worked with schools and young people to prevent and tackle all forms of bullying, including cyberbullying; and £2 million to organisations to specifically prevent and tackle homophobic, biphobic and transphobic (HBT) bullying in schools. This was on top of the £4 million provided for similar projects over the period 2013-15. In March the Government Equalities Office announced that £1 million will be made available to tackle HBT bullying this year.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","38294 ; 38302","2016-06-02T11:48:44.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521159/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521159/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521159/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Pupils: Bullying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what data her Department collects on incidents of peer-to-peer bullying (a) in schools and (b) online.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","38293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521160","Department for Education","false","2016-06-02","<p>It is unacceptable for any child to be victimised, harmed or bullied. All schools are required by law to have a behaviour policy which includes measures to prevent and tackle all forms of bullying. They should exercise their own judgment and develop a consistent approach to monitoring bullying incidents in their school. There is no requirement on schools to record and report incidents of bullying, so the Department does not hold national information on the number of incidents of bullying that take place in schools or online.</p><p> </p><p>The Department provided £1.3 million of funding over twelve months from spring 2015 to three anti-bullying organisations which worked with schools and young people to prevent and tackle all forms of bullying, including cyberbullying; and £2 million to organisations to specifically prevent and tackle homophobic, biphobic and transphobic (HBT) bullying in schools. This was on top of the £4 million provided for similar projects over the period 2013-15. In March the Government Equalities Office announced that £1 million will be made available to tackle HBT bullying this year.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","38293 ; 38302","2016-06-02T11:48:44.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521160/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521160/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521160/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Pupils: Bullying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what data for recording peer-to-peer bullying by schoolchildren (a) in schools and (b) online exist (i) nationally and (ii) locally.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","38294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521161","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>The information is available in Table 1b of the Main tables:SFR46/2015 spreadsheet found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2015-to-2016</a></p><p> </p><p>Column D of this table shows the total percentage contribution of new entrants to the yearly trainee teacher recruitment target for the last six years.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-06T16:54:16.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521161/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521161/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521161/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the degree to which trainee teacher recruitment has met her Department's targets in each of the last five years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","38346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521162","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department for Education pays annual salaries. These have been converted to hourly rates using the calculation ((Gross Basic Salary*FTE)/52)/Weekly hours:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Mar-15</p></td><td><p>Mar-16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>BME</p></td><td><p>£19.22</p></td><td><p>£19.32</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-BME</p></td><td><p>£21.67</p></td><td><p>£22.00</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T15:56:14.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521162/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521162/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521162/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Department for Education: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the average hourly earnings were of her Department's (a) BME and (b) non-BME employees in (i) 2015 and (ii) 2016.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","38218"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521163","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>The information requested is not collected by the Department.</p><p> </p><p>Whilst we know from the annual School Workforce Census how many teachers are teaching Other Modern Foreign Languages in secondary schools, we cannot identify how many are teaching Mandarin.</p><p> </p><p>Following the Chancellor’s announcement last September of a £10 million fund for Mandarin teaching in English schools, the Department is starting a Mandarin Excellence Programme in September 2016 with the aim of teaching Mandarin Chinese to a high level to at least 5,000 pupils by 2020. This programme will ensure that there is a sufficient number of teachers for these pupils.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-06T16:48:00.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521163/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521163/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521163/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Mandarin Language: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many Mandarin language teachers are working in schools; and how many people are training to teach the Mandarin language.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","38243"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521164","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>The number of academies which have been graded inadequate by Ofsted and have not re-brokered to another academy sponsor in each year since 2010 is shown in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Academic year</p></td><td><p>Number of academies in category 4</p></td><td><p>Number of academies not re-brokered to another academy sponsor</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>27</p></td><td><p>21</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>45</p></td><td><p>28</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>94</p></td><td><p>61</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>92</p></td><td><p>69</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September–December 2015*</p></td><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>*Data for 2016 is not available</p><p> </p><p>The Education and Adoption Act 2016 gives the Secretary of State consistent powers to terminate funding agreements where an academy is rated inadequate by Ofsted or has fallen within the definition of coasting. Regional Schools Commissioners can use these powers to move an academy to a new sponsor where they think this is necessary.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-06T16:35:18.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521164/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521164/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521164/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Academies: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many academy schools which have been given an inadequate Ofsted rating in each year since 2010 have not been re-brokered to another academy sponsor.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","38244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521165","Department for Education","false","2016-06-02","<p>The Department does not collect information on the number of sexual assaults taking place on school sites, and is not able to estimate the numbers of them occurring.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-02T11:38:34.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521165/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521165/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521165/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Schools: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 23 May 2016 to Question 37395, if she will estimate the number of cases of sexual assault recorded in schools in England in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","38202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521166","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>The information requested is available in Table 1a of the Main tables: SFR46/2015 found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/initial-teacher-training-trainee-number-census-2015-to-2016</a></p><p>This table shows the number of postgraduates recruited to Initial Teacher Training in the academic year 2015/16 by route and subject, including mathematics and physics.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-06T16:42:19.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521166/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521166/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521166/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many (a) mathematics and (b) physics teachers completed teacher training through each available teacher training route in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","38182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521167","Department for Education","false","2016-06-06","<p>A list of free school projects that were cancelled or withdrawn between 2011 and 2015, and that have final confirmed expenditure, is published on GOV.UK at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/523706/Free_Schools_Data_for_Publication.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/523706/Free_Schools_Data_for_Publication.xlsx</a>.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-06T14:05:14.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521167/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521167/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521167/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-24","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many free schools projects have been cancelled at any stage in each year since 2011.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","38181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521168","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-05-26","<p>Business rates are calculated based on a property’s ‘rateable value’. The Valuation Office Agency (VOA) is responsible for determining the rateable values in line with existing legislation and case law.</p><p> </p><p>The VOA is currently consulting with the solar industry over how those rateable values will apply to solar installations from 1st April 2017.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-05-26T14:33:02.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521168/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521168/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/521168/answer",,,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-05-24","Solar Power: Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she has made of the effect on the solar industry of the Valuation Office Agency's proposals to increase business rates for solar PV FIT and RO installations dating back to 2010.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","38163"
