"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520642","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>I am pleased to report that over 1,200 young people in Staffordshire have participated in NCS over the past two years. The NCS Trust does not collect data at a constituency level. Therefore, the figures below are for the local authority area of Staffordshire:</p><p>2014 - 465 participants<br>2015 - 738 participants</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-05-27T13:42:00.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520642/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520642/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many young people in Stafford constituency participated in the National Citizen Service in each of the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jeremy Lefroy","Stafford","Jeremy Lefroy","37898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520643","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-31","<p>Information on expenditure on food is not held separately to overall expenditure on catering, hospitality and subsistence, which is normally sold with no subsidy.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-31T09:32:06.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520643/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520643/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Cabinet Office: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much is spent from the public purse on food procured for (a) his Department and (b) the Prime Minister's Office; and what proportion of food procured for each was sourced from British producers in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","37901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520644","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>The new arrangements agreed with Crown Dependencies and Overseas Territories with finance centres, giving UK law enforcement and tax authorities quick and unrestricted access to beneficial ownership information on corporate and legal entities incorporated in these jurisdictions, must be in place by June 2017. UK law enforcement authorities will, however, work with these jurisdictions to ensure that the spirit of the arrangements is respected immediately.</p><p>Anguilla committed to these arrangements via an Exchange of Notes with the UK on 19 April. The signing of the arrangement with Guernsey is expected shortly following their recent general election and formation of a new government. Implementation of the arrangement is anticipated to follow the same timescale as above.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-06-09T10:53:44.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520644/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520644/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Companies: Anguilla and Guernsey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Answer of 11 May 2016 to Question 36368, what timescale Anguilla and Guernsey have given for putting in place central registers of beneficial ownership or similarly effective systems.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520645","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-26","<p>The Government published details of the cost of the producing, distributing and publicising its EU Referendum leaflet and associated website on 6th April 2016</p><p><br>The total cost was £9.3 million, with the breakdown of these costs as follows:<br>• production – £458,500<br>• print and delivery to over 27 million homes across the UK in 2 waves – £5,947,436<br>• digital promotion and website – £2,894,064</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-05-26T17:01:16.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520645/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520645/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","UK Membership of EU: Referendums","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the cost to the public purse has been of all advertising of the Government's position on the EU referendum on social media to date.","false","Biography information for Tim Loughton","East Worthing and Shoreham","Tim Loughton","37839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520646","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-26","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-05-26T15:17:50.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520646/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520646/answer","UKSA response to 37879 (2).pdf","UKSA response to 37879 (2).pdf","Referral Letter","Referral Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520646/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Zero Hours Contracts: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many people under the age of 25 in (a) England, (b) Greater Manchester and (c) Manchester, Withington constituency are employed on zero-hours contracts.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","37879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520647","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>The Anti-Corruption Champion attended the anti-corruption summit on 12 May and hosted a delegate’s breakfast. He also addressed the Tackling Corruption Together conference, organised by civil society and business, and attended a reception for summit delegates at No10 Downing Street the day before. In addition, he had a number of bilateral meetings with some of the delegates.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","37820","2016-05-27T12:54:27.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520647/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520647/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what role the Anti-Corruption Tsar had in the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520648","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>Eva Joly MEP was invited in an expert capacity and attended one of the panel discussions. Ms Joly is a renowned Franco-Norwegian Judge who joined the High Court of Paris in 1990 as an investigating judge to lead a number of high-profile corruption cases.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-27T13:03:30.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520648/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520648/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Anti-corruption Summit: European Parliament Members","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, which Members of the European Parliament were invited to the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520649","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>The Anti-Corruption Champion co-chairs the Inter Ministerial Group on Anti-Corruption, which oversees the government’s work to tackle corruption domestically and internationally</p><p><br>Officials from the Cabinet Office provide support to the Group and the Anti-Corruption Champion as part of wider Anti-Corruption work.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-27T12:59:01.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520649/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520649/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Anti-corruption Champion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what funding the Government provides its Anti-Corruption Tsar to tackle corruption.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37887"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520650","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>The Anti-Corruption Champion attended the anti-corruption summit on 12 May and hosted a delegate’s breakfast. He also addressed the Tackling Corruption Together conference, organised by civil society and business, and attended a reception for summit delegates at No10 Downing Street the day before. In addition, he had a number of bilateral meetings with some of the delegates.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","37849","2016-05-27T12:54:27.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520650/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520650/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Anti-corruption Summit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government's Anti-Corruption Tsar addressed the Anti-Corruption Summit on 12 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520651","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office manages the UK's relationship with the Overseas Territories, and the Ministry of Justice manages the relationship with the Crown Dependencies. The Anti-Corruption Champion is in close contact with both departments on those issues that relate to his work.</p><p>The details of visits will be published in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-27T13:05:20.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520651/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520651/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Anti-corruption Champion: Crown Dependencies and British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what visits the Government's Anti-Corruption Tsar has taken in an official capacity to the British Overseas Territories and Crown dependencies since his appointment to that role.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520652","Cabinet Office","false","2016-05-27","<p>The full costs of the preparation and delivery of the Anti-Corruption Summit are still to be confirmed and this information will be made available in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-05-27T12:57:04.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520652/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520652/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-05-23","Corruption: Conferences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, with reference to the Answer of 10 May 2016 to Question 36307, what the total cost was of (a) the Anti-Corruption Summit held on 12 May 2016 and (b) the Tackling Corruption Together Conference held on 11 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","37797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520653","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-26","<p>HMRC receives enquiries from Hon Members about tax credit awards in a number of different ways. HMRC seeks to answer every one as a high priority. No comprehensive figures are held for the time taken to answer all enquiries.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-05-26T15:39:31.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520653/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520653/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many enquiries have been made by hon. Members to HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) on tax credits claims in the last 12 months; and what the average time taken was for HMRC to respond to those enquiries.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","37798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520654","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-01","<p>The Treasury does not procure food directly for the Department. The catering facilities are provided by an external company engaged by the Private Finance Initiative (PFI) management company. The catering contract is run on a nil subsidy and therefore is of no cost to the Department. The catering provider is obligated to follow the cross government requirements of sourcing its produce under Red Tractor guidelines.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-06-01T16:17:28.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520654/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520654/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Treasury: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the annual budget is for food produced for his Department's offices; and what proportion of food produced for his Department was sourced from British producers in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","37836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520655","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-27","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","37945","2016-05-27T13:25:39.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520655/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520655/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Social Security Benefits: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of annual claims made for (a) tax credits and (b) child benefit by EU nationals who remain in the UK for less than one year in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","37943"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520656","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-01","<p>No estimate has been made of the cost of providing public services for EU nationals who remain in the UK for less than one year.</p><p> </p><p>The Government’s ambition is to reduce permanent migration into this country to a more manageable level.</p><p> </p><p>We remain committed to bringing migration down to sustainable levels, which is in the best interests of our country. The Government has taken steps to control migration by dealing with those who shouldn't be here, by deporting illegal immigrants and improving the skills of British workers, so we reduce the demand for skilled migrants.</p><p> </p><p>The Prime Minister has re-negotiated the UK’s position within the EU to close back-door routes into the UK and exert greater control over EU migration by tackling the draw of our welfare system.</p><p> </p><p>But net migration remains too high and there is still more work to do.</p><p> </p><p>Data recently released by HMRC showed recently-arrived EU migrants paid £2.5 billion more in tax than they received in tax credits or child benefit in 2013/14.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-06-01T16:05:00.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520656/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520656/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520656/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Public Sector: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the cost of providing public services for EU nationals who remain in the UK for less than one year.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","37944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520657","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-27","<p>The information requested is not available.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","37943","2016-05-27T13:25:39.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520657/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520657/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Income Tax: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the income tax paid each year by EU nationals who remain in the UK for less than one year in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","37945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520658","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-26","<p>The Lifetime ISA is a voluntary product. For further information on the costing of this policy, please see page 9 of the Budget 2015 Policy Costings document: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/508147/PU1912_Policy_Costings_FINAL3.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/508147/PU1912_Policy_Costings_FINAL3.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>ISA statistics are published on the GOV.UK website. Table 9.7 sets out the number of individuals subscribing to ISAs by income and amount subscribed: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/number-of-individuals-subscribing-to-an-individual-savings-account-isa-by-income" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/number-of-individuals-subscribing-to-an-individual-savings-account-isa-by-income</a>.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-26T10:53:56.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520658/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520658/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Individual Savings Accounts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Answer of 11 May 2016 to Question 36241, what assumptions were made about the number of people (a) taking up a Lifetime ISA and (b) subscribing the maximum annual amount to an ordinary ISA in calculating the estimated Exchequer impacts set out in that Answer.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","37929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520659","HM Treasury","false","2016-06-01","<p>‘Additional funding’ has been interpreted to mean welfare expenditure. There is no policy of additional welfare expenditure for nationals of other EU member states who remain in the UK for less than one year.</p><p> </p><p>If the UK votes to remain in the EU, the Prime Minister’s February deal will take effect. Included in the deal is the ‘Emergency Brake’, a mechanism to exclude recently-arrived EEA workers from access to full UK in-work benefits for 4 years. Initially the Brake will involve complete exclusion for in work benefits. The deal also confirmed that in future the UK will not have to pay any means-tested unemployment benefits to EU nationals who come to the UK as job seekers.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-06-01T14:13:29.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520659/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520659/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Local Government Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether it is his Department's policy to provide additional funding to local authorities for providing public services for nationals of other EU member states who remain in the UK for less than one year; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","37942"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520660","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-26","<p>The changes to tax relief for travel and subsistence only affect those who work through an employment intermediary. The planned changes will put supply teachers employed through an intermediary on the same terms as other supply teachers, either contracted directly, or through an agency contract.</p><p> </p><p>The Government’s general assessment of the effects of the measure can be found in the Tax Information and Impact Note: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-tax-employment-intermediaries-and-relief-for-travel-and-subsistence/income-tax-employment-intermediaries-and-relief-for-travel-and-subsistence" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/income-tax-employment-intermediaries-and-relief-for-travel-and-subsistence/income-tax-employment-intermediaries-and-relief-for-travel-and-subsistence</a></p><p> </p><p>The Government undertook detailed consultation on these proposals. Further assessment can be found in the summary of responses to the consultation document published on this change: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/483389/Employment_Intermediaries_and_Tax_Relief_for_Travel_and_Subsistence_-_Summary_of_Responses__M7057_.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/483389/Employment_Intermediaries_and_Tax_Relief_for_Travel_and_Subsistence_-_Summary_of_Responses__M7057_.pdf</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-26T13:03:06.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520660/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520660/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Supply Teachers: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect on supply teachers of new restrictions on tax relief for travel and subsistence expenses for workers engaged through an employment intermediary.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","37899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520661","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-26","<p>We welcome the statement from the source of the Panama Papers that they are willing to speak to law enforcement bodies. Tax evasion and money laundering are global issues, which is why the HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) and National Crime Agency (NCA) taskforce is working with international tax and law enforcement partners to take up this offer, and develop as many leads as possible from the data that is currently available.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC has been in regular contact with the International Consortium of Investigative Journalists (ICIJ), who have refused to share their full data with HMRC, stating that their policy is not to hand over such material. While we welcome the steps the ICIJ has taken in exposing this issue, its decision not to release the full set of information is disappointing.</p><p> </p><p>HMRC has begun analytical work on all the data published by the ICIJ, in addition to a wide range of other intelligence. As a result of this, the HMRC and NCA taskforce has opened a number of detailed and forensic enquiries.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-26T10:48:06.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520661/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520661/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Mossack Fonseca","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations his Department have received from the International Consortium of Investigative Journalists (ICIJ) on the list of addresses of British entities registered with the Mossack Fonseca law firm in Panama published by the ICIJ on their website on 9 May 2016.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","37976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520662","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-26","<p>NS&amp;I has no current plans to move roles it has in the UK to Chennai.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-05-26T10:56:31.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520662/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520662/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","National Savings and Investments: India","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the (a) number, (b) current responsibilities and (c) current locations are of the roles which National Savings and Investment plans to move to Chennai.","true","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","38066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520663","HM Treasury","false","2016-05-26","<p>HM Revenue and Customs has based its decisions on the locations of the future regional centres on a number of key principles including retention of its current staff and skills, access to a pipeline of talent and local and national transport links. In this context it will be locating its Regional Centre for Yorkshire and the Humber in Leeds.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-05-26T10:44:59.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520663/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520663/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520663/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-05-23","Revenue and Customs: Bradford","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will publish the business case on the closure of the HM Revenue and Customs offices in Bradford.","false","Biography information for Judith Cummins","Bradford South","Judith Cummins","38067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520664","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-26","<p>The National Planning Policy Framework and planning guidance requires local authorities to plan for a mix of housing based on current and future demographic trends, and the needs of different groups in their area. This includes housing suitable for occupation by elderly people.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-05-26T13:35:55.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520664/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520664/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-05-23","Housing: Older People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure that there is a sufficient supply of single-storey housing for occupation by elderly people; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","38073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520665","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-05-26","<p>Our policy is that every coastal community should have the chance to bid for a share of the Coastal Communities Fund to help them with projects that will have a real and lasting impact on their local economy. The 118 Coastal Community Teams (CCTs) in England now provide an important new local context for considering these bids, so that the Fund helps to deliver community-led Economic Plans. Each bid is considered on its merits and allocating the Fund to regions on the basis of their population share would not necessarily ensure best value for money.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2016-05-26T16:37:39.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520665/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520665/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-05-23","Coastal Communities Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 9 May 2016 to Question 36275, if he will make it his policy to ensure that disbursements from the Coastal Communities Fund are allocated to the regions of England on the basis of population share.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","37969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520666","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-06-01","<p>The Department for Communities and Local Government does not have an annual food budget. Catering services are provided via a contract with Interserve Plc, and is operated on a nil subsidy basis.</p><p>Annual spend is determined by the contractor and is informed by private sales to members of staff.</p><p>Approximately 34% of products across all food and drink categories were sourced from British producers as at March 2016.This proportion reflects that a large volume of food and drink sold includes non-indigenous products such as rice, pasta, tea, coffee and bananas, and that as this period falls in the Winter season there are out of UK seasonal products procured from the wider EU.</p><p>The proportion also reflects consumer trends, and the commercial contractor’s pursuit of value for money given the nil subsidy arrangement.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2016-06-01T15:31:32.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520666/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520666/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520666/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-05-23","Department for Communities and Local Government: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the annual budget is for food produced for his Department's offices; and what proportion of food produced for his Department was sourced from British producers in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","37824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520667","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-06","<p>The Department does not set a budget for food served in its offices. Catering is available to the department but this is not managed by DCMS. Figures are not available for food purchased by staff for their own use.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-06-06T16:09:01.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520667/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520667/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520667/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-05-23","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the annual budget is for food produced for his Department's offices; and what proportion of food produced for his Department was sourced from British producers in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","37825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520668","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-26","<p>Over the last two financial years, Welcome to Yorkshire has received a total of ​£1,619,100 of Government funding to promote tourism and the success of cycling in Yorkshire, building on the Grand Depart.</p><p> </p><p>This Government is providing £1.5million funding for the Ferens gallery in Hull so it can host the 2017 Turner prize.</p><p> </p><p>And in 2014, the Canal River Trust won £450,000 from the Cycling Ambition in National Park programme for a range of cycling schemes, including the transformation of a 4km stretch of the Leeds and Liverpool Canal centred on the market town of Skipton, which is also a key gateway to the Yorkshire Dales.</p><p> </p><p>On 24 May Government announced funding for both the Sustainable Travel Transition Year Fund 2016/17, and the North East Lincolnshire and Lincolnshire, with projects earmarked across the region but not in the specific Yorkshire Dales area.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-05-26T09:13:55.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520668/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520668/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520668/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-05-23","Leisure: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what Government funding has been awarded to (a) Welcome to Yorkshire, (b) the campaign to bring the Turner Prize to Hull in 2017 and (c) the creation of a new cycle gateway to the Yorkshire Dales National Park since the publication of the Long-Term Economic Plan for Yorkshire and North Lincolnshire in February 2015.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","37811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520669","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-05-26","<p>Freedom City 2017 is an important and exciting prospect for Newcastle-upon-Tyne. Arts Council England's (ACE) North Director in Newcastle sits on the steering group for the festival and, in April 2015, ACE provided a Grants for the arts award of £15,000 to the Northern Roots, a partner in the development of the Freedom City 2017 event. ACE are continuing discussions with the Festival organisers on how they can further support the event.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-05-26T12:15:12.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520669/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520669/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520669/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-05-23","Festivals and Special Occasions: Newcastle upon Tyne","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans he has to support Newcastle upon Tyne's Freedom City 2017 festival.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","37956"
