"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520717","Department for Education","false","2016-06-01","<p>The Department currently funds two training programmes delivered by the Future Leaders Trust (FLT): the High Potential Senior Leaders programme and the Talented Leaders Programme.</p><p> </p><p>94% of teachers who have participated in the High Potential Senior Leaders programme in the last three years are now in headship or senior leadership posts. This figure includes participants in their first, second or final year of the programme.</p><p> </p><p>In August 2014, FLT was awarded the contract to deliver the Talented Leaders Programme. The first cohort in 2015 was made up of 16 participants. As of May 2016, 100% of these are still in post as head teachers.</p><p> </p><p>FLT also delivered a pilot programme of the Multi-Academy Trusts (MAT) CEO course for 23 participants. Recent analysis shows that all participants were still in leadership posts in MATs or similar educational organisations.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-01T14:50:52.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520717/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520717/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-05-23","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of teachers who have participated in The Future Leaders Trust programmes in the last three years are now in senior leadership posts.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","37909"
