"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520853","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The Department funds Public Health England to undertake a range of social marketing campaigns to support behaviour change and public awareness. This work will be funded within the annual budget as will the work on other infections, such as influenza, as well as non-infectious diseases. Further planning work will be undertaken to determine the budget for this activity.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-05-26T16:08:38.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520853/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520853/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-23","Infectious Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much funding his Department will make available for Public Health England's awareness campaign on the symptoms of serious infections; and what proportion of that funding will be spent on sepsis awareness.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","38044"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520854","Home Office","false","2016-06-06","<p>The UK Government takes it’s responsibility in all cases involving children seriously and we will continue to ensure that all unaccompanied children are provided with appropriate care, regardless of their route to the UK.</p><p>It is important that we work with local authorities to understand their capacity to support all unaccompanied children and ensure their needs can be met. That is why my officials are working closely with the Department for Communities and Local Government and the Department for Education to ensure consultation with local authorities is consistent and coordinated across all resettlement and relocation programmes. Consultation with local government partners will take place over the coming weeks and Parliament will be updated in due course.</p><p>We are keen to ensure that there is a more equitable distribution of unaccompanied children across the UK and that no local authority is required to take more children than they can support.</p><p>The Home Office provides funding to local authorities for the care of unaccompanied asylum seeking children and recently announced new enhanced rates to support the transfer scheme. We will continue to measure the impacts on local authorities, but are clear that funding for unaccompanied asylum seeking children and refugees must be aligned, regardless of the route of entry for the child.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","37889 ; 38014","2016-06-06T17:04:36.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520854/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520854/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-05-23","Refugees: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what plans the Government has to publish the outcome of its consultation with local authorities on the resettling of child refugees under the Immigration Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","38028"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520855","Home Office","false","2016-06-06","<p>The average time taken between January 2015 and December 2015 to consider whether an application meets the fee waiver requirements is 95 calendar days. These results represent the time taken with both asylum and non asylum based fee waiver considerations.</p><p>January 2015 – December 2015 was taken as the 12 month time frame to fall in line with data that is published.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-06T16:38:46.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520855/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520855/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-05-23","Immigration: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken was to decide fee waiver applications in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","38022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520856","Home Office","false","2016-06-06","<p>The average time taken between January 2015 and December 2015 to consider whether an application meets the requirements to change a condition code is 83 calendar days.</p><p>January 2015 – December 2015 was taken as the 12 month time frame to fall in line with data that is published.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-06T15:58:29.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520856/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520856/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-05-23","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken was to decide applications for the change of conditions of leave granted on the basis of family or private life during the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","38020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520857","Home Office","false","2016-06-06","<p>There are no service standards for fee waiver applications.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-06T16:40:52.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520857/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/520857/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-05-23","Immigration: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department has service standards in place for considering fee waiver applications.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Smith","Oxford East","Mr Andrew Smith","38023"
